+[[writing-tests-display-name-generator-extensions]]
+==== Extensions of Display Name Generators
+The class DisplayNameGenerator already supports the extensions of `Standard`
+`ReplaceUnderscores` and `IndicativeSentences`.
+
+By using the annotation `@DisplayNameGenerator` that sends as parameter
+`ReplaceUnderscores.class`:
+
+`@DisplayNameGeneration(DisplayNameGenerator.ReplaceUnderscores.class)`
+
+You can replace the class and methods names under the naming convention
+`test_separated_by_underscore`, and converting it on the output text.
+With this you can avoid the use of `@DisplayName` and get a prettier
+output tests results.
+
+Also, by using the annotation `@DisplayNameGenerator` that sends as parameter
+`IndicativeSentences.class`:
+
+`@DisplayNameGeneration(DisplayNameGenerator.IndicativeSentences.class)`
+
+You can generate an output that concatenates the names of your tests
+and the enclosing parents, in this way making  the results more indicative
+and easy to read, using this annotation will use by default `Standard` as
+generator and ", " as separator.
+
+We can optionally customize the DisplayNameGenerator and the separator
+between the sentences, by setting the parameters `separator` followed by a
+string and `generator` followed by a `DisplayNameGenerator` class:
+
+`@IndicativeSentencesGeneration(separator = " >> ", generator =
+ReplaceUnderscores.class)`
